member.summary:
            Initializes a new System.Key instance by an array of objects. Types supported to initialize a System.Key object include:

1. all system integers, numbers and their array/list (except System.Decimal and its array/list);

2. System.Char and its array/list;

3. System.DateTime and its array/list;

4. System.String and its array/list (encoded by Unicode); 

5. a struct whose size is able to be determined by System.Runtime.InteropServices.Marshal.SizeOf method (however, array/list of structs is not supported);

6. any other type that has a method named ToBytes.

Returns a value neither larger than 
nor smaller than .
If the current value is neither smaller than  nor larger than , then the  itself will be returned;
if the current value is larger than , then  will be returned;
if the current value is smaller than , then  will be returned.

Returns a value not smaller than .
If the current value is not smaller than , then the  itself will be returned;
if the current value is smaller than , then  will be returned.

Returns a value not larger than .
If the current value is not larger than , then the  itself will be returned;
if the current value is larger than , then  will be returned.

