Specifies the search direction. 
            If this parameter is set true, the search starts at  and ends at the end of this string instance; 
            otherwise, the search starts at  and proceeds toward the beginning of this string instance.

member.summary:
            The search is successful if all the targets are hit sequentially.

For string "aa, bb, cc, dd" as example, if the targets are {"bb", "cc"}, then the search will succeed; 
            if the targets are {"cc", "bb"} the search will fail.
